snippet.textDisplay: i have not been keeping up with kpop in general for a while now. I got really tired of some fans and i didn’t want to admit that i liked kpop . I listen to bts since 2014 now and I have been obsessed for a long time but one day I just didn’t feel the same. I always looked at them and their music from a bit of a different view. I always wanted good for the boys because i know how much korean idols suffer to get to perfection and when bts started to gain more and more fans it just got ridiculous. I always admired their music that where calmer because the message behind was always so strong and deep. Fake love is till this day my favourite song. It means so much to me. They never failed to surprice and never failed with continuing their job. Even tho sometimes you want to see your idol take a break,, its bts and they are just power machines. Seeing them create a song like that, doing a combination of both traditional and modern music style, singing with this muchh passion is just what makes me feel like a proud mother. I love to admire their commitment and I just love to keep up with maybe not everything that bts does but i sure am present at all comebacks. This comeback hit different. It’s almost as if it was wings coming to me again but now it’s just... something more. Just by this one song I can tell that what Namjoon said at the grammys was true. It’s gonna be fuckin hard my armys and I freaking love it!!! Sendig so much love to bts and armys~ remember guys - they deserve what every human does,, let them do their job as they want and dont get dissapointed at some little things. They’re great forever
